<item>
            <title>[SOLR-13362] SolrJ&apos;s LukeRequest should support &quot;includeIndexFieldFlags&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-13362</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7799&quot; title=&quot;LukeRequestHandler too slow when there are many fields&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7799&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-7799&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduces the query-param flag &quot;includeIndexFieldFlags&quot;, which tells Solr that the index flags aren&apos;t needed and can be skipped.  Fetching these flags takes some time, so specifying &lt;tt&gt;includeIndexFieldFlags=false&lt;/tt&gt; on requests can save some time for if users don&apos;t need that information and have collections with a lot of fields.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Support for this flag was never added to the SolrJ class used to trigger requests to Luke though.  It&apos;s a pain to use the flag in SolrJ as LukeRequest is currently written.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
